title: Independent Candidate Musawar Khan wins PK-24 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Musawar Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-24, Malakand-II by securing 43,193 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Syed Muhammad Ali Shah who bagged 22,198 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 43.59 per cent.
